value.value: Volume of blood plasma delivered to a single glomerulus per unit time
Force exerted on the luminal capillary wall from fluid flowing through the capillary.

definition.value: Any measurement of one of the small blood vessels carrying blood between arteries and capillaries.

value.value: Resistance that must be overcome to push blood through arterioles to create flow.
Resistance to blood flow measured within the efferent arteriole proximal to a glomerular capillary network.

definition.value: Resistance to blood flow measured within the afferent arteriole distal to a glomerular capillary network.
Total resistance to blood flow measured within the afferent arteriole proximal and distal to a glomerular capillary network (Rt = Ra + Re).
Measurement of the total amount of all proteins found in a specific volume of afferent arteriolar plasma.
Measurement of the total amount of all proteins found in a specific volume of efferent arteriolar plasma.

value.value: A form of osmotic pressure exerted by proteins, notably albumin, in the afferent arteriole's plasma that tends to pull water into the circulatory system. It is the opposing force to hydrostatic pressure. It has a major effect on the pressure across the glomerular filter.

A form of osmotic pressure exerted by proteins, notably albumin, in the efferent arteriole's plasma that tends to pull water into the circulatory system. It is the opposing force to hydrostatic pressure. It has a major effect on the pressure across the glomerular filter

A measure of a membrane's permeability to water; specifically, the volume of fluid filtered in unit time through a unit area of membrane per unit pressure difference, and it is defined as the glomerular filtration rate (GFR) for both kidneys per millimeter of mercury (mmHg) of filtration pressure.

label.value: ratio of the area occupied by cysts to the total area of the kidney

definition.value: A calculated measurement in which the area occupied by renal cysts is divided by the total the kidney, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.
Blood measurement of Angiotensin I, a decapeptide that is cleaved from precursor angiotensinogen by renin. It is converted to angiotensin II by angiotensin converting enzyme.
Plasma measurement of Angiotensin I, a decapeptide that is cleaved from precursor angiotensinogen by renin. It is converted to angiotensin II by angiotensin converting enzyme.
Serum measurement of Angiotensin I, a decapeptide that is cleaved from precursor angiotensinogen by renin. It is converted to angiotensin II by angiotensin converting enzyme.
Force exerted on the luminal surface of the proximal tubule from fluid flowing through the tubule.

value.value: Force exerted on the luminal vessel wall from fluid flowing through the efferent arteriole.

definition.value: The difference between the force exerted on the luminal glomerular capillary wall and the force exerted on the luminal proximal tubular membrane (Pgc - Pt = delta P).

label.value: retroperitoneal fat pad weight to tibia length ratio
inguinal fat pad weight to tibia length ratio
calculated left ventricular end-diastolic blood pressure measurement
heart left ventricular end-diastolic blood pressure to heart left ventricular end-diastolic diameter ratio

definition.value: A calculated measurement in which the pressure in the heart left ventricle at the end of diastole, the period when the heart is in a state of relaxation and expansion and the ventricles fill with blood, divided by the diameter across the left ventricle of the heart at the end of diastole and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

value.value: Rate-pressure product is defined as the product of the heart rate (the number of contractions of the cardiac ventricles per unit of time) (beats per minute) and mean arterial blood pressure (the average force the blood exerts on an artery wall) (mm Hg).

label.value: liver weight to tibia length ratio

definition.value: A calculated measurement in which the weight of the liver is divided by the length of tibia, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thus normalizing it to body weight and, by extension, to the size of the organism.

A calculated measurement in which the weight of the pancreas is divided by the length of tibia, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thus normalizing it to body weight and, by extension, to the size of the organism.

label.value: urine sodium level to body weight ratio

definition.value: A calculated measurement in which the amount of sodium ions present in a specified volume of urine , is divided by the total weight of the body, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thus normalizing it to body weight and, by extension, to the size of the organism.

label.value: urine potassium level to body weight ratio

definition.value: A calculated measurement in which the amount of potassium ions present in a specified volume of urine , is divided by the total weight of the body, and the result presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage, thus normalizing it to body weight and, by extension, to the size of the organism.

label.value: urine sodium level to urine potassium level ratio

definition.value: A calculated measurement in which the amount of sodium ions present in a specified volume of urine , is divided by the amount of potassium in a specified volume of urine.

label.value: blood insulin level AUC to blood glucose level AUC ratio

value.value: The calculated value blood insulin level area under curve divided by the calculated blood glucose level area under curve. Area under the curve for blood glucose or insulin is a value in which a series of measurements of the amount of insulin or glucose in a specified volume of blood is plotted against time for a single individual and the extent of the two dimensional region bounded by the curve and the axes of the graph is determined.

A calculated measurement to estimate the effect of insulin on net glucose disposal (insulin sensitivity) in an organism, calculated as 10000/(sqaure root of ((fasting glucose x fasting insulin) x (mean glucose across duration of glucose tolerance test x mean insulin across duration of glucose tolerance test).

label.value: Homeostatic Model Assessment of Insulin Resistance

value.value: Calculated model of insulin resistance where the product of fasting glucose and fasting insulin is divided by 22.5. Glucose is measured in mmol/L and insulin in measured in uIU/ml.

The amount of hesperetin found in a specified volume of blood. Hesperetin belongs to the flavanone class of flavonoids. Hesperetin, in the form of its glycoside Hesperidin, is the predominant flavonoid in lemons and oranges.

The amount of hesperetin found in a specified volume of plasma, the fibrinogen-containing fluid portion of the blood in which the particulate components are suspended.Hesperetin, in the form of its glycoside Hesperidin, is the predominant flavonoid in lemons and oranges.

The amount of hesperetin found in a specified volume of serum, the clear liquid that separates from blood after it has clotted completely, i.e. blood plasma from which fibrinogen has been removed. Hesperetin, in the form of its glycoside Hesperidin, is the predominant flavonoid in lemons and oranges.

definition.value: Amount of glucose-6-phophatase measured in a specified sample of liver.
Amount of glucokinase measured in a specified sample of liver.

label.value: calculated serum high density lipoprotein cholesterol level

definition.value: A measurement of the amount of high density lipoprotein cholesterol in serum which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation. Cholesterol is a eukaryotic sterol that in higher animals is the precursor of bile acids and steroid hormones and a key constituent of cell membranes, is carried in high-density lipoprotein (HDL) molecules. High density lipoprotein cholesterol refers to any of a group of conjugated proteins that have at least one lipid component.

label.value: serum high density lipoprotein cholesterol level to serum total cholesterol level ratio

value.value: A calculated measurement in which the amount of HDL cholesterol in a specified volume of serum is divided by the amount of total serum cholesterol, without taking into account any association with other molecules such as lipoproteins, in a specified volume of serum, in the same sample, and presented as a ratio, fraction, quotient or percentage.

definition.value: Quantitation of the catalytic effect exerted by dipeptidyl-peptidase 4 (DPP4) in a specified volume of blood. Dpp4 is a cell surface glycoprotein receptor involved in the costimulatory signal essential for T-cell receptor (TCR)-mediated T-cell activation.

Quantitation of the catalytic effect exerted by dipeptidyl-peptidase IV (DPP4) in a specified volume of plasma. Dpp4 is a cell surface glycoprotein receptor involved in the costimulatory signal essential for T-cell receptor (TCR)-mediated T-cell activation.

Quantitation of the catalytic effect exerted by dipeptidyl-peptidase IV (DPP4) in a specified volume of serum. Dpp4 is a cell surface glycoprotein receptor involved in the costimulatory signal essential for T-cell receptor (TCR)-mediated T-cell activation.

label.value: artery tunica media to artery total diameter ratio

definition.value: A calculated measurement of the average width of the tunica media (the middle coat of the arterial wall) divided by the artery total diameter (measured as the length of a line which crosses a transverse view of an artery, passing through its center and ending on either side at the outer surface of the blood vessel wall).

label.value: artery lumen to artery total diameter ratio

definition.value: A calculated measurement of the average width of the artery lumen (measured as the length of a line which crosses a transverse view of an artery, passing through its center and ending on either side at the inner surface of the blood vessel wall) divided by the artery total diameter (measured as the length of a line which crosses a transverse view of an artery, passing through its center and ending on either side at the outer surface of the blood vessel wall).

value.value: Measurement of the morphological characteristics of the gastrointestinal tract. The gastrointestinal tract is an organ system within humans and other animals which takes in food, digests it to extract and absorb energy and nutrients, and expels the remaining waste as feces. The mouth, esophagus, stomach and intestines are part of the gastrointestinal tract.

Measurement of the weight or heaviness of the gastrointestinal tract, that is, the degree to which it is drawn toward the earth by gravity. The gastrointestinal tract is an organ system within humans and other animals which takes in food, digests it to extract and absorb energy and nutrients, and expels the remaining waste as feces. The mouth, esophagus, stomach and intestines are part of the gastrointestinal tract.

definition.value: A measurement of the weight of the gastrointestinal tract which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation.
